"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn scatterplot function already includes a legend by default if the hue parameter is used. However, in this case, the hue parameter is not used, so the ax.legend() call is unnecessary and will result in an empty legend being displayed. To fix this, the ax.legend() call should be removed.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7,8c7\\n< sbn.scatterplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', ax=ax)\\n< ax.legend()\\n---\\n> sbn.scatterplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', ax=ax)\\n\"\n}"